content:
After you complete setup, CRM Analytics Direct Data for Data Cloud lets you create and run queries on Data Cloud records in real time. You can also build dashboard charts and tables based on these queries.

To add a chart that shows customer orders by product category:

In the dashboard designer, click Create Query or add a chart widget and click it.
Click Salesforce Data Cloud to build the query on a Data Cloud data source.
Select a Data Cloud data source containing order data. Data Cloud data is categorized into source types:
Data Lake Objects
Data Models
Calculated Insights

Group orders by product category in the lens that opens, then add total spend and number of orders as measures in the chart. Sort the chart by total spend.

For advanced queries, switch to Query mode and write custom SQL queries against Data Cloud records.

To save changes to the dashboard, click Done.
title: Building Queries with CRM Analytics Direct Data for Data Cloud
